21/04/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- A meeting of the justice and interior ministers of the EU member countries and countries of Southeast Europe will take place in Thessaloniki on Tuesday (22 April).
The main issues will be border control, the fight against organised crime, and regional migration and asylum.
In other news, Sarajevo will host an international conference next week, officially opening the Interreg 3A Cross-Border Adriatic Programme.
Diplomats from BiH, Italy, Albania, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro are expected to attend.
They will discuss regional development and co-operation.
(Anadolu Agency - 21/04/03;
Dnevnik - 20/04/03;
HINA, BBC - 18/04/03)
